REPS.groupDesc: Out of all your customers, 75% of them do not come back for a second purchase. To address this issue, run camapaigns for the customers who did not come back for 56 days, after their first visit.

RFV.groupDesc: Hibernators are customers who are the verge of being lapsed. You need to run a targeted campaign to win these back before they become lapsedAdvocates are your best customers. Increase the category penetration with these customers with a cross-sell campaignNascent Shoppers are in their initial stages with you. Use the response to campaigns to ascertain the best product to advertise to them.

FS.groupDesc: Out of all customers, top 1.8% of them ,2165, visit more than 3 times, and 11481 customers visit only once. Sherlock recommends that you start having targeted campaigns for these customers based on their last purchased product. Also run frequency bulding campaigns for Low and Mid Frequency customers, with appropriate incentivisation. Lower the visits, higher the incentive. Chances of repeat for a customer after first visit is 25.3%. The chances of repeat for a customer after second visit is 37.9$.

VS.groupDesc: Out of all customers, top 3.9% of them ,4658, spend more than 3330 Rupees, and 4796 customers spend less than 1495 Rupees. Sherlock recommends that you start running cross-sell and up-sell campaigns for the Low frequency and Mid frequency customers. Also run campaigns based on recommendation engine.

NALS.groupDesc: Out of all repeating customers, 25% of them repeat within 37 days. Also 50% of repeating customers, repeat within 155 days. Any customer who was acquired in the last 37 days is termed as a New Customers. Any customer who did not visit for the last 155 days is considered as a Lapsed Customer.

DS.groupDesc: Out of all your customers, 175439 of them did not opt for a discount. Their affinity to discount needs to be evaluated with their response of being sent a campaign.Also 114777 have made purchases only with a discount coupon, of these 17441 have made more than one purchase. High discount seekers and full discount seekers, are likely to respond only for a discount campaign. Mid discount seekers and Low discount seekers might place more emphasis on relevance than discount. A customer who bought less than 50% of products on discount is termed as a Low Discount Seeker. While any customer who purchased atleast 65% of products on discount is termed as a High Discount Seeker.These groups are formed basis the discount seeking behavior of your customers.
